Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Mott Smith test problem", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9334043059496875`*^9, 3.9334043136954947`*^9}, {
  3.9334043730189486`*^9, 3.9334043759706955`*^9}, {3.934256631519663*^9, 
  3.9342566391361303`*^9}},
 FontSize->24,ExpressionUUID->"9ca98b98-77fe-485a-b5ea-3fa6bfbd7642"],

Cell["\<\
This code test prediction quality of the Gramian and extended Gramian \
closures for the (n + 1)^th
moment given the set of n lower moments. We consider the description of shock \
waves in gas dynamics and given by the well-known Mott-Smith distribution. We \
compare the moment prediction with Grad\[CloseCurlyQuote]s closure and \
maximum entropy closure.  Details about Gramian and extended Gramian closures \
with different test problems can be found in the following paper  \
https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.05894\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9334043797824507`*^9, 3.933404388342066*^9}, {
  3.9339065760670166`*^9, 3.9339065778042517`*^9}, {3.933907321765495*^9, 
  3.9339073439639626`*^9}, {3.933907589544405*^9, 3.933907685063188*^9}, {
  3.933907738235751*^9, 3.9339078044023657`*^9}, {3.9339078598785706`*^9, 
  3.9339079506807203`*^9}, {3.9342566865481653`*^9, 
  3.934256715634451*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f9ea3e97-2d82-4698-89fb-\
d2aa666d566e"],

